[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(5) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Go out unto the cities of Judah, and gather of all Israel money.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—This is the chronicler’s interpretation of “Let the priests take it to themselves, each from his own acquaintance” (Kings). The priests and Levites of the different districts were to collect the moneys due to the sanctuary, each in his own neighbourhood.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And see that ye hasten the matter.—Literally, and, for your part, hasten ye in regard to the matter (comp. 2Chronicles 18:8); and the Levites hastened not. This agrees with the statement in 2Kings 12:6; 2Kings 12:9 : “And it was so, that in the three and twentieth year of king Jehoash the priests had not repaired the breaches of the house.” The remissness of the priestly order is evidently inferable from these words.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "And see that ye hasten the matter.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Literally, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "and, for your part, hasten ye in regard to the matter",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " (comp. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2Chronicles 18:8",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "); ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "and the Levites hastened not.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " This agrees with the statement in ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2Kings 12:6",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2Kings 12:9",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " : “And it was so, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "that in the three and twentieth year of king Jehoash",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " the priests had not repaired the breaches of the house.” The remissness of the priestly order is evidently inferable from these words.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 24:5",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Chronicles 24:5",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Gather of all Israel — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Not only of the tribes of Judah and Benjamin, but of all the Israelites, belonging to any of the ten tribes, who are now resident in my kingdom: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "money to repair, &c., from year to year",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " — That is, either, 1st, To repair part of it every year till the reparations were perfected: or, 2d, The money was to be gathered from year to year, till they got such a sum as might suffice for the work.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
