          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "2. Gather it from year to year, till you get such a sum as may suffice for the work; for he supposed one or two years’ collection would not suffice for the work, whether it were that collection of half a shekel for every man, of which see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Exodus 30:12,13 2 Kings 12:14",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Exodus 30:12",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ",13 ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Kings 12:14",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; or a voluntary contribution required for the present exigence of the temple by virtue of the command and example of Moses, who made such a collection for the building of the tabernacle, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Exodus 35:5",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Exodus 35:5",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; see also ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Nehemiah 10:32",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Nehemiah 10:32",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; which he thought would not be any great sum, because of the great iniquity and impiety which yet had reigned for many years, and yet continued in the generality of the people of the land, the Levites not excepted, as the last clause of this verse shows. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
